    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>HYUNDAI REVISES REVAMPING PLAN</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Samuel Len</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Len, Samuel</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bowing to pressure from creditors, Hyundai Group of South Korea expects to release new business plan to spin off its automobile-related units; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Bowing to pressure from creditors, the Hyundai Group of South Korea said it expected to release a new plan to spin off its auto-related business units. The company said the proposal would include splitting off the Hyundai Motor Company from the group, after lowering the 9.1 percent stake held by the Hyundai Group founder Chung Ju Yung to less than 3 percent, as the government has been requesting. Mr. Chung, meanwhile, was hospitalized suffering from what company officials called fatigue.</p>
        <p>Samuel Len</p>
      </block>
